  "prompt": "What is it like to immigrate to New Zealand?",
  "response": "Immigrating to New Zealand involves several key aspects:\n\n1. Visa Process\n- Requires obtaining appropriate visa/work permit\n- Skilled migrant categories are most common\n- Points-based system evaluates qualifications, work experience, age\n- Can be competitive and time-consuming\n\n2. Economic Considerations\n- Generally good job market for skilled professionals\n- Cost of living is moderate\n- Healthcare and education systems are high quality\n- Wages are competitive\n\n3. Cultural Experience\n- Welcoming and multicultural society\n- Strong emphasis on work-life balance\n- Friendly population, known as \"Kiwis\"\n- Bicultural society respecting M\u0101ori culture\n\n4. Quality of Life\n- Beautiful natural landscapes\n- Low population density\n- Safe environment\n- Good social welfare system\n\n5. Challenges\n- Relatively isolated geographically\n- Initial cost of establishing life can be high\n- Distance from other countries\n- Competitive housing market, especially in cities like Auckland\n\n6. Requirements\n- English language proficiency\n- Health checks\n- Background checks\n- Proof of skills/qualifications\n- Sufficient financial resources\n\nOverall, immigration is possible but requires careful planning, meeting specific criteria, and adapting to a new cultural environment.",
